definition.value: A monohydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid with a alpha-hydroxy substituent at position 3. It is a bile acid obtained from chenodeoxycholic acid by bacterial action.
Any hexose-1-phosphate which has D configuration at position 5 and alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.
A dicarboxylic acid monoamide that is  succinamic acid substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
